postcontent: I have a model 720 savage for sale.  It is 12 gauge and in very good condition.  John Browning allowed Savage and Remington to make shotguns on his patented Browning A5 design.  The 720 was manufactured between 1930 and 1949.  The serail # on this one would give it an approximate date of '39, though not for certain.  It is a plain barrel, 29" and appears to be a fine shooter, though I haven't shot it.  It is very similar to the Remington Model 11 and the A5 Browning.  I've been told that they perform identically to the A5.  The 720 like the A5 is a long recoil shotgun, meaning the barrel and bolt slide together to eject the spent shell.  Many of these were sold to the military for training purposes and are stamped with an "M" next to the model #.  This is not the military version.  $375 obo.  More pictures available on request.
